properties.name: Line 65 (LSR Project)
properties.description: "Line 65 is a 20-inch-diameter crude oil pipeline, originating at Enbridge's Cromer Terminal near Cromer, MB, and terminating at Enbridge's Clearbrook Terminal near Clearbrook, MN." (from corporate website)
properties.capacity: 186,000 barrels per day, light and medium crude

properties.name: Chicap
properties.description: "The Chicap Pipeline consists of 203 miles of 26-inch-diameter mainline from Patoka, IL to Manhattan/Mokena, IL; 12 miles of 16-inch-diameter pipe from Mokena to Lemont, IL; and 15 miles of 14-inch-line from Mokena to Blue Island, IL. Enbridge has a 43.8-percent ownership interest in the pipeline, which is operated by BP."(from corporate website)
properties.capacity: "360,000 barrels per day (Patoka to Manhattan/Mokena); 100,000 barrels per day (Mokena to Lemont)"

properties.name: Line 9 / Canadian Mainline
properties.description: "Line 9 is a 30-inch-diameter crude oil pipeline, originating at Sarnia, ON, and terminating at Montreal, QC. The section known as Line 9A travels from Sarnia to Enbridge’s Westover Station near Hamilton, ON, while the section known as Line 9B travels from Westover Station to Montreal, QC."(from corporate website)

properties.name: Ozark Pipeline
properties.description: The pipeline from Cushing to Wood River, IL, was previously owned by Enbridge and known as Line 51. MPLX bought it in 2017 and extended it from Wood River to Patoka.

properties.name: Mustang
properties.description: The pipeline runs from the Chicago area (Lockport) to Patoka.

properties.name: Nanticoke
properties.description: 47-mile pipeline running from the company's Westover Station to Nanticoke, ON.

properties.name: Seaway Pipeline System
properties.description: "The Seaway system includes a 500-mile, 30-inch diameter pipeline between Cushing, Oklahoma and the Freeport, Texas area, and a terminal and distribution crude oil network originating in Texas City, Texas that serves all of the refineries in the Greater Houston area" (from corporate website). The pipeline is a reversal, later doubled.

properties.name: North Line
properties.description: The ipeline originates in St James, and moves up to northern Louisiana servicing various refineries.

properties.name: LOOP/LOCAP Pipeline
properties.description: The pipeline connects the company's terminal in St James to its underground salt-dome storage facility near Clovelly - the largest in the US. From there it heads out into the Gulf. With the announced 2020 reversal of the third-party Capline that terminates in St James, the LOOP/LOCAP pipeline is positioned as a crucial connector, potentially making its terminus at the Loousiana Offshore Oil Port into a massive export terminal for crude from the Bakken and the Alberta Tar Sands.
properties.capacity: 1.7 million barrels per day, expandable to 2.3 mb/d.

properties.name: Longhorn
properties.description: The pipeline runs from Permian gathering points around Odessa TX to Houston.

properties.name: Osage
properties.description: "This 135-mile pipeline, which FERC regulates, supplies HFC's El Dorado Refinery with crude oil from Cushing, Oklahoma and also has a connection to the Jayhawk pipeline that services the CHS refinery in McPherson, Kansas. HEP has a 50% interest in this entity and is the operator of the pipeline." (source here)
